The paper deals with wireless networks and energy-efficiency, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The introduction of hierarchy in the power control games involves game theory (cs.GT). The use of decentralized multiple access channels and successive interference cancellation suggests that the paper may also belong to the networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a way of measuring the global performance of the network, which could be related to machine learning (cs.MA).
